2012, I heard about this new
education company called Udacity.

24
00:01:16,050 --> 00:01:18,640
That was actually what the logo
looked like at the time.

25
00:01:18,640 --> 00:01:22,700
I didn't know much about it, but online
education sounded really interesting, so

26
00:01:22,700 --> 00:01:24,420
I emailed someone who worked there.

27
00:01:24,420 --> 00:01:26,860
Three days later,
I was on a plane to San Francisco.

28
00:01:26,860 --> 00:01:28,570
It was very exciting.

29
00:01:28,570 --> 00:01:31,490
But things at Udacity were
pretty chaotic back then, and

30
00:01:31,490 --> 00:01:33,890
